  "prompt": "Is there such a thing as an agnostic theist?",
  "response": "Yes, an agnostic theist is someone who believes in the existence of a deity or deities (theism) but also acknowledges that the nature and existence of this deity or deities cannot be known or proven (agnosticism). In other words, an agnostic theist holds a belief in God or gods while simultaneously admitting that such beliefs cannot be substantiated with absolute certainty. This position combines elements of both faith and skepticism.",
